      <strong>The University of Cambridge's</strong> wide-ranging and long-term 
      strategy of engagement with African higher education institutions moved 
      into its next phase following the recent announcement of a $1.2 million 
      grant by the Carnegie Corporation of New York and a $1 million grant by 
      The Alborada Trust.<br />
      more information <a href="http://news.admin.cam.ac.uk/news/2012/08/03/grants-take-cambridge-in-africa-programme-to-next-level/">here</a><br />
